Combine water and sugar.  Add flour and sprinkle yeast on top.  Mix with dough hook until smooth, then knead for 10 minutes
on low speed.  Let rise until doubled.  Portion into 2.5-oz balls.  Place into greased perforated 2" steam pans.  (At this point you
may cover the pans and place in cooler overnight.  Take out early enough for them to rise before baking.)  Let rise again.  Place
in preheated steamer and steam for about 15 minutes.  They should be served very soon after steaming.
Raspberry jam is yummy with these steam buns.
